lows/workflow_strategies/`: reusable workflow strategy implementations. Put iteration logic, workflow decision-making, and prompt sequencing here.\n--- ./tests/src/AGENTS.md\n# Instructions when developing tests\n\n## Code Style\n- Tests should throw and assert against standard Java exceptions; do not use `GradleException` in test code.\n- The model may modify `buildArgs` in `build.gradle` only in `graalvmNative` and only to add `--add-opens` or `--add-exports arguments`.rg: src: No such file or directory (os error 2)\nmetadata/cglib/cglib/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/cglib/cglib/$version$/cglib-$version$-sources.jar\",\nmetadata/cglib/cglib/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/cglib/cglib\",\nmetadata/cglib/cglib/index.json:7:    \"test-code-url\" : \"https://github.com/cglib/cglib/tree/RELEASE_3_3_0/cglib/src/test/java\",\nmetadata/cglib/cglib/index.json:8:    \"documentation-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/cglib/cglib/$version$/cglib-$version$-javadoc.jar\",\nmetadata/cglib/cglib/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"cglib is a bytecode generation library for creating subclasses and implementations of Java classes and interfaces at runtime. It is commonly used by frameworks to build dynamic proxies, method interceptors, and other runtime-generated types.\",\nmetadata/cglib/cglib/index.json:14:      \"net.sf.cglib\"\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777809541735}]}
