 process**\\n\\nI'm considering what happens if static initialization occurs at build time without build arguments. The native-image process requires certain opens, so I might need to add them to the agent for Java run. The `tasks.withType(Test)` will include agent mode, which is good. I need to ensure that the file name `NetSfCglibCoreReflectUtilsTest` correctly maps to the active class. There might be issues with untracked metadata, especially if we add a new file, but that could mean it requires reachability metadata. Also, I’m looking into how to manage borrowed generated bytes and class names efficiently in my tests.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class generation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using a generated class in the CGLIB package for clarity. I need to change the class bytes, but I'm not sure if I can generate them with `javac` since I can't run that. Manual creation of bytes could work too. Using ASM in tests sounds promising, but it might get too specific. Also, using static class bytes from another example seems odd. Maybe I can create those bytes using CGLIB’s repackaged ASM, since CGLIB depends on `org.ow2.asm`. Let’s see how that goes!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Compiling Java Classes**\\n\\nI'm thinking about creating a temporary Java file and compiling it with the current JDK to get its bytes in base64. However, I have to consider that version 69 might not be supported by JDK21. Instead, I could use `javac --release 8` to produce a compatible version. My goal is to generate the class `cglib.cglib.ReflectUtilsGeneratedFixture`. So, I’ll proceed with `javac --release 8` and handle encoding from there. This is more of a development command rather than for tests.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FOZ5sXGKvuyNw824OznaKJHs|fc_0bce82438a9b6c150169f73929bc688196991e5d5ca7b243f4", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); mkdir -p \"$tmp/cglib/cglib\"; cat > \"$tmp/cglib/cglib/ReflectUtilsGeneratedFixture.java\" <<'JAVA'\npackage cglib.cglib;\n\npublic class ReflectUtilsGeneratedFixture {\n}\nJAVA\njavac --release 8 -d \"$tmp/out\" \"$tmp/cglib/cglib/ReflectUtilsGeneratedFixture.java\"\nbase64 \"$tmp/out/cglib/cglib/ReflectUtilsGeneratedFixture.class\"", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2574, "output": 957, "cacheRead": 40960, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44491, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777809681580, "responseId": "resp_0bce82438a9b6c150169f73912099c8196a7628c3683ba8f13"}}
